FBIS4-45954 "jptnd012___94046" JPRS-TND-94-012 JPRS PROLIFERATION ISSUES 16 May 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA INDIA Tanks Get Advanced Fire, Explosion Suppression System Tanks Get Advanced Fire, Explosion Suppression System BK1605102994 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 GMT 16 May 94 BK1605102994 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] The Defense Institute for Fire Research in New Delhi has developed a fire fighting system that can detect and put out fires in less than one-fourth of a second. The director of the institute, Major General B.S. Kataria, said the automatic fire and explosion suppression system, as it is called, has been fitted on the MBT [Main Battle Tank]-Arjun tank and is to be fitted also on the T-72 tanks. He said this fire fighting system has been integrated with another system to alert the tank crew in the event of a nuclear, biological, and chemical attack. The fire protection system can also be fitted in ships and armored personnel carriers.
